text: Sian Rainsley is a triathlete from Great Britain. She was born on 19 April 1997. Rainsley competed at the 2014 Youth Olympic Games and won a silver medal, 2021 European Triathlon Championships and won a bronze medal. == References == == Other websites == Category:1997 births Category:British athletes Category:Living people Category:Triathletes Category:People with Crohn's disease
